swSredMIB.name: swSredMIB
swSredMIB.description: The structure of Simple RED Information for the proprietary enterprise.

swSredGlobalState.name: swSredGlobalState
swSredGlobalState.description: This object enables\disables the Simple RED state of the device.

swSredDropCounterTable.name: swSredDropCounterTable
swSredDropCounterTable.description: A table that contains SRED drop packet counter information for each port.

swSredDropCounterEntry.name: swSredDropCounterEntry
swSredDropCounterEntry.description: A list that contains SRED drop packet counter information per port.

swSredPortIndex.name: swSredPortIndex
swSredPortIndex.description: This object indicates the port number.

swSredLowDropCounter.name: swSredLowDropCounter
swSredLowDropCounter.description: This object indicates the drop count at low threshold.

swSredHighDropCounter.name: swSredHighDropCounter
swSredHighDropCounter.description: This object indicates the drop count at high threshold.

swSredCtrlTable.name: swSredCtrlTable
swSredCtrlTable.description: A table that contains the SRED setting for each port.

swSredCtrlEntry.name: swSredCtrlEntry
swSredCtrlEntry.description: A list that contains SRED setting per port.

swSredCtrlPortIndex.name: swSredCtrlPortIndex
swSredCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the port number.

swSredCtrlClassIndex.name: swSredCtrlClassIndex
swSredCtrlClassIndex.description: This object indicates the hardware CoS queues the config sred command will apply to.

swSredCtrlThresholdLow.name: swSredCtrlThresholdLow
swSredCtrlThresholdLow.description: This object indicates the low threshold that specifies the percentage of space utilized.

swSredCtrlThresholdHigh.name: swSredCtrlThresholdHigh
swSredCtrlThresholdHigh.description: This object indicates the high threshold that specifies the percentage of queue space utilized.

swSredCtrlDropRateLow.name: swSredCtrlDropRateLow
swSredCtrlDropRateLow.description: This object indicates the probabilistic drop rate if above the low threshold.

swSredCtrlDropRateHigh.name: swSredCtrlDropRateHigh
swSredCtrlDropRateHigh.description: This object indicates the probabilistic drop rate if above the high threshold.

swSredCtrlDropGreenState.name: swSredCtrlDropGreenState
swSredCtrlDropGreenState.description: This object indicates the drop green state. Setting this state to be disabled means probabilistic drop red colored packets if the queue depth is above the low threshold, and probabilistic drop yellow colored packets if the queue depth is above the high threshold. Setting this state to be enabled means probabilistic drop yellow and red colored packets if the queue depth is above the low threshold, and probabilistic drop green colored packets if the queue depth is above the high threshold.

sw8021pColorMapCtrlTable.name: sw8021pColorMapCtrlTable
sw8021pColorMapCtrlTable.description: A table that contains information about priority map to packet color on each port.

sw8021pColorMapCtrlEntry.name: sw8021pColorMapCtrlEntry
sw8021pColorMapCtrlEntry.description: A list that contains priority map to packet color on per port.

sw8021pColorMapCtrlPortIndex.name: sw8021pColorMapCtrlPortIndex
sw8021pColorMapCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the port number.

sw8021pColorMapCtrlPriorityIndex.name: sw8021pColorMapCtrlPriorityIndex
sw8021pColorMapCtrlPriorityIndex.description: This object indicates the source priority of incoming packets.

sw8021pColorMapCtrlColor.name: sw8021pColorMapCtrlColor
sw8021pColorMapCtrlColor.description: This object indicates the source priority of incoming packets.

swDscpTrustPortCtrlTable.name: swDscpTrustPortCtrlTable
swDscpTrustPortCtrlTable.description: A table that contains information about the DSCP trust portlist.

swDscpTrustPortCtrlEntry.name: swDscpTrustPortCtrlEntry
swDscpTrustPortCtrlEntry.description: A list that contains the DSCP trusted state per port.

swDscpTrustPortCtrlPortIndex.name: swDscpTrustPortCtrlPortIndex
swDscpTrustPortCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the port number.

swDscpTrustPortCtrlState.name: swDscpTrustPortCtrlState
swDscpTrustPortCtrlState.description: This object is used to enable/disable the DSCP trusted state on a selected port.

swDscpMapCtrlTable.name: swDscpMapCtrlTable
swDscpMapCtrlTable.description: A table that contains information about DSCP map to priority and packet color on each port.

swDscpMapCtrlEntry.name: swDscpMapCtrlEntry
swDscpMapCtrlEntry.description: A list that contains DSCP map information for each port.

swDscpMapCtrlPortIndex.name: swDscpMapCtrlPortIndex
swDscpMapCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the port number.

swDscpMapCtrlDscpIndex.name: swDscpMapCtrlDscpIndex
swDscpMapCtrlDscpIndex.description: This object indicates the source DSCP incoming packet.

swDscpMapCtrl8021pPriority.name: swDscpMapCtrl8021pPriority
swDscpMapCtrl8021pPriority.description: This object indicates the 802.1p priority on each port. Default value is: DSCP Priority 0-7 0 8-15 1 16-23 2 24-31 3 32-39 4 40-47 5 48-55 6 56-63 7

swDscpMapCtrlNewDscp.name: swDscpMapCtrlNewDscp
swDscpMapCtrlNewDscp.description: This object indicates the new DSCP map on each port.

swDscpMapCtrlColor.name: swDscpMapCtrlColor
swDscpMapCtrlColor.description: This object maps the color for packets on each port.
